                            <comment id="13267983" author="tucu00" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 00:34:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;being a bit conservative, the AuthenticationFilter will not trust the AuthenticationHandler to set the UNAUTHORIZED response when returning NULL and it will set it itself (if happens twice is a NOP).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13267991" author="atm" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 00:56:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 pending Jenkins. The patch looks good to me. I also tested the patch manually and observed that the spurious stack traces no longer appear in the NN or 2NN logs when performing a checkpoint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good on you, Tucu.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
